sub_fields.label: Tab Content
sub_fields.name: tab_content
sub_fields.default_value: Screen printing, also sometimes known as silkscreen printing, is the process of pressing ink through a stencilled mesh screen onto a substrate, usually t-shirts, to create a printed design. The thick ink lays on top of the shirt rather than soaking in and one colour is printed at a time, so several screens can be used to produce a multicoloured image or design.
